begin_memory_text: We introduced ourselves and said where we lived and she told me that she was a med student in Ohio and I told her I worked as an analyst.  I noticed she had a cat.  It was just basic introductions.
middle_memory_text: We talked about the fact that my husband and her best friend had submarines in common.  Her best friend is currently stationed where my husband was stationed when he was on a submarine.  We talked about where she was from and how far it was from where she is attending med school.  I told her where I went to college and about how I studied psychology and counseling there but ended up in a completely different career.
end_memory_text: We talked about how her med school does A&P labs differently than other med school labs in that they're virtual. She told me about how realistic it seemed and how certain parts in the body could be color coded so the students could easily tell what they were supposed to be looking at.  I told her a story about my best friend's experience when she had a cadaver lab years ago.  She told me her dad was an OB/GYN which is why she's always been interested in being one herself.
rest_of_day_open: I think the rest of my week will be good, but busy.  My parents are coming to visit tomorrow and staying for the rest of the weekend so it will be nice to get some quality time with them.  We'll go see my daughter cheer at a game tomorrow evening and then the rest of the weekend we're going to try to get some things done around the house, watch college football, shop, and hopefully do some bike riding as well.
critical_positive: We were able to find a few things in each of our lives that had a common thread to them.  She's in medical school and my best friend is a doctor.  Her best friend is currently on a submarine.  My husband was a submarine officer.  With those shared close connections it was easy to make conversation flow.
critical_negative: I really felt like everything worked well.  There were just a couple of short pauses in the conversation where I think both of us were trying to think of what to say next, but they were quick and one of us would think of another question to ask and the conversation immediately picked back up with ease.  There really was nothing that didn't go well.

begin_memory_text: Where we're from, what we do, and what paths we took to get us here in our lives. We found out that her husband and my best friend work in the same niche field!
middle_memory_text: We talked about the field (navy submarines) that her husband and my best friend are both in. We found out that they overlapped in many of the same cities, which was such a small world coincidence.
end_memory_text: We talked about where she went to college, where I went to college, and medical school during a pandemic. In particular, we discussed my virtual reality anatomy curriculum for a while.
rest_of_day_open: The rest of my week is busy with school work to finish up and two long afternoon shifts at work on Thursday and Friday. However, I am really looking forward to a volunteer experience that I have on Saturday morning! I am also planning to carve a pumpkin this weekend which should be fun.
critical_positive: I think the conversation worked really well because we felt like we both had a lot in common. We were both familiar with the life circumstances of the other person, which made it easy to ask questions and stay interested in the conversation topics. We were also both very open-minded and fun to talk to.
critical_negative: The only thing I can think of that didn't work in the conversation was that we were unsure of how to begin at first. In particular, I wasn't sure how much personal information I should share with someone on the internet, but as I felt more comfortable speaking with her, I felt less concerned.
